data.title: 150 TOP YOUTUBE GAMING INFLUENCERS IN 2024 (UPDATED)
data.meta_description: These are 150 top YouTube gaming influencers in 2024. These YouTube gamers have most consumer impact on the gaming industry.
data.text:
The Witcher 3: Wild Hunt developer, CD Projekt Red’s anti-piracy strategy of offering DRM/Denuvo-free games is largely based on the goodwill they enjoy among the gamers. The success of their strategy is reflected in the large number of PC sales (~12 million) for Witcher 3. Also, according to North American Technographies Consumer Life Cycle Survey, approximately 70% consumers are more likely to purchase a product with positive customer reviews. This indicates the significance of customer trust & goodwill in the gaming industry and particularly the role of Youtube gamers on the customer acquisition journey. All this catapults to growing relevance of influencer marketing, as top influencers enjoy a high degree of trust with their user base, providing brands with great customer goodwill.

Influencer marketing also enables brands to make informed marketing decisions based on the number of followers, social media engagement rates, number of likes/comments, etc. Such parameters serve as Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) allowing companies to choose the influencers they need & monitor their progress in real-time.

These are among the countless other advantages that influencer marketing enjoys over conventional marketing strategies. With the influencer marketing industry set to achieve the milestone of over 16.4 Billion USD by 2024, our top gaming marketing agency compiled a list of 100 top Youtube gaming influencers in 2024, designed to help brands in their search of finding the perfect influencer for their marketing objectives!

150 Top YouTube Gaming Influencers (Best Gaming Youtubers) in 2024:

1. PewDiePie (Top 10 Gaming)

Felix Arvid Ulf Kjellberg, widely recognized as PewDiePie, has amassed an astonishing subscriber count exceeding 111 million on his YouTube channel alone, making him one of the most subscribed creators on the platform. Beyond YouTube, PewDiePie has garnered millions of followers on platforms such as Twitch, Twitter, Instagram, and TikTok, further solidifying his status as a gaming influencer powerhouse. His ‘Let’s Play’ commentaries, horror playthroughs and reactions in the gaming space have been the hallmark of his channel. In 2022, the content producer and streamer has had his fair share of controversy and turmoil, but he remains one of the internet’s most direct characters. Following his achievement of a hundred million subscribers in 2019, the star’s rise to prominence as a top content provider appears to have slowed this year. On Twitter, a conversation thread erupted, with followers offering their opinions on the matter.

Throughout his career, PewDiePie has collaborated with numerous renowned brands, showcasing his versatility and appeal to a wide range of audiences. Some of his notable brand partnerships include collaborations with gaming companies like Ubisoft, EA, and Activision, as well as endorsements from brands outside the gaming industry, such as clothing lines, energy drinks, and tech companies.

In 2019, PewDiePie found himself embroiled in another controversy when he made inflammatory remarks during a livestream, prompting criticism from both fans and fellow creators. While PewDiePie issued apologies and explanations for his behavior, the incident reignited discussions about accountability and responsibility in the online content creation community.

Despite these controversies, PewDiePie has managed to maintain his position as one of the most influential figures in the gaming industry, with his content continuing to attract millions of views and engagements. His ability to navigate challenges and adapt to changing trends underscores his resilience and enduring appeal to audiences worldwide.

2. JuegaGerman (Top 10 Gaming)

Expanding on gaming influencers, in addition to PewDiePie, German Alejandro Garmendia Aranis, commonly known as JuegaGerman, has emerged as a prominent figure in the gaming community. With an impressive subscriber count of 40.1 million on YouTube, JuegaGerman specializes in uploading commentaries on various video games, with a particular focus on titles like The Walking Dead. His channel stands out for its consistent content creation, boasting an average view count of 3.22 million per video, solidifying his status as one of the top gaming influencers on the platform.

JuegaGerman’s success extends beyond his subscriber count, as his channel’s net value reached a substantial $7.1 million dollars as of April 2022. Born in 1990 and residing in Chile, JuegaGerman has become a leading figure in the gaming YouTube community, consistently ranked among the top 10 gaming YouTubers on social media platforms in 2024.

In terms of brand partnerships and collaborations, JuegaGerman has worked with a variety of companies within and outside the gaming industry. Gaming giants such as Ubisoft, Capcom, and Bethesda are among the notable brands that have partnered with JuegaGerman to promote their games and products. Additionally, JuegaGerman’s influence extends beyond gaming, as he has collaborated with brands in sectors like tech, entertainment, and lifestyle, showcasing his versatility and appeal to diverse audiences.

Despite the competitive landscape of online content creation, JuegaGerman’s consistent output of engaging content and his ability to connect with his audience have solidified his position as a leading gaming influencer. As he continues to evolve his content and engage with his fans, JuegaGerman remains a formidable force in the gaming community, leaving a lasting impact on the industry for years to come.

3. elrubiusOMG (Top 10 Gaming)

Expanding on the profile of Ruben Doblas Gundersen, also known as ElRubius, sheds light on his significant influence in the gaming YouTube community. With an impressive subscriber count of 40+ million, ElRubius has cemented his position as one of the foremost gaming content creators on the platform. His channel, renowned for its engaging gameplay videos and insightful blogs, consistently attracts a wide audience of gaming enthusiasts.

In addition to his content creation endeavors, ElRubius remains highly active and involved in 2024, particularly with his contribution to gamerstats.net’s “ElRubius’s Streaming Setup: Gaming Setup and PC Specs.” This initiative showcases ElRubius’s commitment to providing valuable insights and resources to aspiring content creators, offering detailed information about his gaming setup, PC specifications, and streaming gear.

Furthermore, ElRubius continues to expand his brand and influence through strategic partnerships and collaborations with leading gaming and tech companies. Brands such as Razer, ASUS ROG, and Corsair are among the notable collaborators that have recognized ElRubius’s reach and impact, partnering with him to promote their gaming gear and products. These collaborations not only enhance ElRubius’s credibility within the gaming community but also provide his audience with access to high-quality gaming equipment endorsed by their favorite content creator.

On April 20, 2022, ElRubius unveiled his new collection, which includes a wide range of gaming gear, gaming PC setups, streaming equipment, and insights into the costs associated with building a setup similar to his own. This release demonstrates ElRubius’s commitment to sharing his expertise and passion for gaming with his audience, while also providing valuable resources for aspiring gamers and content creators alike.

MrBeast’s net worth is $55 million dollars. His entire fortune stems from his internet enterprises, which include his YouTube channels, MrBeast official shop, and others. MrBeast, better known as Jimmy Donaldson, has over one million subscribers in May 2017. MrBeast now has over 93 million customers (as of April 2022).
